    {
      "id": "76521151-36f2-46e8-b1b9-ac0ba6335911",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Despite its effectiveness in math education, self-explanations seem to be an underused source of data about student learning processes. However, with new advancements in NLP it may now be possible to use them. Thus, the authors propose the use of an LLM to automatically grade mathematical self-explanations and provide personalzied feedback based on them. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "76521151-36f2-46e8-b1b9-ac0ba6335911",
        "parent": {
