    {
      "id": "17b5cd47-a01f-41c4-aaba-0e57b95ba704",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Authors use 5 distinct datasets for validation. Results show that combining LLM explanations with amthematical material improves the accuracy of such an auto-grader model. Authors also find that there is a cap in synthetic self-explanations before the model starts to overfit.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "17b5cd47-a01f-41c4-aaba-0e57b95ba704",
        "parent": {
